issue.title: No work mapdrv with Wondertang in V9990 mode
issue.body:
To reproduce it

Wondertang, flashed in V9990 mode with the file

Nextor-2.1.3.MegaFlashSDSCC.1-slot.ROM or . Nextor-2.1.2.MegaFlashSDSCC.1-slot.ROM

Once we have basic, we create the partitions on a 16GB SD card, 4 partitions.

In the first partition, we put content and the latest versions of Nextor.

We boot, and drive A: is mapped alone with the first partition.

If we run mapdrv c: 2 or combinations of mapdrv c: 2 1 0, for example, it doesn't always give a drive error (which works in MSX).

If we remap the partition with drive A:

mapdrv a: 2 , the system drive stops mounting and mounts a: on the second partition of the SD card.

in wondertang normal firmware, work correctly

How should we map the other partitions?

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8a8c784e-5f47-4a5c-aa74-28d7cbbe4a37)

comment.body:
Here is a question. Lets imagine a world where that was the real Etienne Lux was just walking around with people who could kill him with a thought despite being an omnipath that can puppet literally anyone to act as his stand in.

If you killed him would he truly take millions with him? He would obviously threaten genocide upon his death as a deterrent to stop people from murdering him but would he actually carry it out. Consider the moment of his death, what would killing all those people achieve? It would show his threats have meaning but that would be irrelevant as he would no longer be in a position to threaten anyone. It would be pointless and thus immoral. Thus I don't think they had to go through the trouble, the exact same thing would have happened if they killed him without psychic shielding but I guess best not to take that chance.

issue.title: üö® URGENT: Fix Digger status check names for branch protection
issue.body:
## üö® Urgent Fix Required

This PR fixes the status check naming mismatch that's blocking PR #7 from merging.

## Problem
- Branch protection requires status checks named: `Digger - dev` and `Digger - staging`
- Workflow was creating status checks named: `digger/dev/plan` and `digger/staging/plan`
- GitHub doesn't recognize manually created status checks for branch protection
- PR #7 is BLOCKED despite all work being complete

## Solution
Changes the status check context from:
```javascript
context: `digger/${environment}/${action}`
```

To:
```javascript
context: `Digger - ${environment}`
```

## Impact
- ‚úÖ Fixes the blocking issue for PR #7
- ‚úÖ Future PRs will have correct status check names
- ‚úÖ No other changes or side effects

## Next Steps
1. ‚úÖ Merge this PR to main
2. ‚úÖ Re-trigger Digger on PR #7 with `/digger plan`
3. ‚úÖ PR #7 will be unblocked and ready to merge

**Please merge this immediately to unblock PR #7**
